# Motion & Operator Examples
  |                            |                                              |
  |----------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
  | **Basic Combinations**     |                                              |
  | `dL`                       | delete word forward                          |
  | `cJ`                       | change word backward                         |
  | `y$`                       | yank to end of line                          |
  | `d0`                       | delete to start of line                      |
  | `ci"`                      | change inside quotes                         |
  | `da(`                      | delete around parentheses                    |
  |                            |                                              |
  | **With Counts**            |                                              |
  | `3dL`                      | delete 3 words forward                       |
  | `5dd`                      | delete 5 lines                               |
  | `2yy`                      | yank 2 lines                                 |
  | `4cL`                      | change 4 words forward                       |
  | `10==`                     | auto-format 10 lines                         |
  | `=10i`                     | format 10 lines up                           |
  | `=10k`                     | format 10 lines down                         |
  |                            |                                              |
  | **Formatting**             |                                              |
  | `==`                       | format current line                          |
  | `gg=G`                     | format entire file                           |
  | `=af`                      | format around function                       |
  | `=ac`                      | format around class                          |
  | `5==`                      | format 5 lines                               |
  |                            |                                              |
  | **Treesitter Combos**      |                                              |
  | `daf`                      | delete entire function                       |
  | `yif`                      | yank function body                           |
  | `cic`                      | change class body                            |
  | `daa`                      | delete parameter (with comma)                |
  | `cia`                      | change parameter value                       |
  | `vaf`                      | select entire function                       |
  |                            |                                              |
  | **Navigation Patterns**    |                                              |
  | `␣nf` then `dif`           | jump to next function, delete its body       |
  | `␣pc` then `yac`           | jump to previous class, yank it              |
  | `/search` then `ciq`       | search text, change in quotes                |
  | `gd` then `yaf`            | go to definition, yank function              |
  |                            |                                              |
  | **Complex Examples**       |                                              |
  | `di(` then `p`             | delete args, paste new ones                  |
  | `ciq` then `esc` then `p`  | change quoted text with register             |
  | `␣nf` `␣nf` then `daf`     | skip 2 functions, delete 3rd                 |
  | `vif` then `=`             | select function body, format it              |
  | `␣na` then `daa`           | next parameter, delete it                    |

# Keymap Translation (Custom IJKL vs Classic Vim)

This table helps translate between your IJKL layout and classic vim for tutorials and discussions.

## Movement & Navigation
  | Classic Vim | Your Layout | Function                    | Notes                    |
  |-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|--------------------------|
  | `h`         | `j`         | move left                   |                          |
  | `j`         | `k`         | move down                   |                          |
  | `k`         | `i`         | move up                     |                          |
  | `l`         | `l`         | move right                  | same                     |
  | `w`         | `L`         | word forward                |                          |
  | `b`         | `J`         | word backward               |                          |
  | `e`         | `w`         | end of word                 |                          |
  | `5j`        | `K`         | 5 lines down                |                          |
  | `5k`        | `I`         | 5 lines up                  |                          |

## Insert Mode
  | Classic Vim | Your Layout | Function                    | Notes                    |
  |-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|--------------------------|
  | `i`         | `e`         | insert mode                 | main difference!         |
  | `I`         | `E`         | insert at line start        |                          |
  | `a`         | `a`         | append after cursor         | same                     |
  | `A`         | `A`         | append at line end          | same                     |
  | `o`         | `o`         | open line below             | same                     |
  | `O`         | `O`         | open line above             | same                     |

## Text Objects
  | Classic Vim | Your Layout | Function                    | Notes                    |
  |-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|--------------------------|
  | `iw`        | `sw`        | inner word                  | `i` used for movement    |
  | `iW`        | `sW`        | inner WORD                  |                          |
  | `i(`        | `sp`        | inner parentheses           | AZERTY shortcut          |
  | `i{`        | `sb`        | inner braces                | AZERTY shortcut          |
  | `i[`        | `sr`        | inner brackets              | AZERTY shortcut          |
  | `i"` `i'`   | `i"` `i'`   | inner quotes                | same (via mini.ai)       |
  | `aw`        | `aw`        | around word                 | same                     |
  | `a(` `a{`   | `ap` `ab`   | around parens/braces        | AZERTY shortcuts exist   |

## Window Navigation
  | Classic Vim | Your Layout | Function                    | Notes                    |
  |-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|--------------------------|
  | `<C-w>h`    | `<C-w>j`    | go to left split            |                          |
  | `<C-w>j`    | `<C-w>k`    | go to bottom split          |                          |
  | `<C-w>k`    | `<C-w>i`    | go to upper split           |                          |
  | `<C-w>l`    | `<C-w>l`    | go to right split           | same                     |
  | `<C-w>s`    | `<C-w>h`    | split horizontally          | `h` for horizontal       |
  | `<C-w>v`    | `<C-w>v`    | split vertically            | same                     |

## Visual Mode (Block)
  | Classic Vim | Your Layout | Function                    | Notes                    |
  |-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|--------------------------|
  | `<C-v>I`    | `<C-v>I`    | block insert at start       | same                     |
  | `<C-v>A`    | `<C-v>A`    | block append at end         | same                     |
  | `v` then `I`| `v` then `e`| visual block insert start   | custom binding           |
  | `v` then `A`| `v` then `E`| visual block insert end     | custom binding           |

## Not Remapped (Work the Same)
  | Key         | Function                    | Notes                    |
  |-------------|-----------------------------|--------------------------|
  | `d` `c` `y` | delete/change/yank          | all operators same       |
  | `p` `P`     | paste after/before          | same                     |
  | `u` `<C-r>` | undo/redo                   | same                     |
  | `/` `?`     | search forward/backward     | same                     |
  | `n` `N`     | next/prev search            | same                     |
  | `gg` `G`    | start/end of file           | same                     |
  | `0` `$`     | start/end of line           | same                     |
  | `%`         | matching bracket            | same                     |
  | `*` `#`     | search word under cursor    | same                     |
  | `.`         | repeat last change          | same                     |
  | `dd` `yy`   | delete/yank line            | same                     |
  | `x`         | delete character            | same                     |
  | `r`         | replace character           | same                     |
  | `s`         | substitute character        | same                     |

## Translation Examples

When you see in tutorials:
- `diw` (delete inner word) → use `dsw`
- `ci(` (change in parens) → use `csp` or `ci(`
- `5j` (down 5) → use `K`
- `5k` (up 5) → use `I`
- `w` (word forward) → use `L`
- `b` (word back) → use `J`
- `3w` (3 words forward) → use `3L`
- `i` followed by text → use `e` followed by text
- `<C-w>h` (left split) → use `<C-w>j`
- `<C-w>j` (down split) → use `<C-w>k`
- `<C-w>k` (up split) → use `<C-w>i`

# Tips
- Movement uses IJKL instead of HJKL (AZERTY-friendly)
- Use `e` instead of `i` to enter insert mode
- Use `;` instead of `:` for command mode (easier on AZERTY)
- Press `␣?` to see all available keybindings with which-key
- See translation table above when following classic vim tutorials


# Motions
- Text objects: Use `sw` instead of `iw` (since `i` is movement)
- Numbers work as multipliers: `3L` = 3 words forward, `5dd` = delete 5 lines
- Combine operators with motions: `d3L` = delete 3 words, `c$` = change to end of line
- Treesitter textobjects only work in operator-pending or visual mode (after d/c/y/v)
- Format operations: `=` works with any motion or textobject
- Chain navigation + operations: jump to location, then operate on textobject



# vim: ft=markdown
